Package org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.mapping.config

Class CPrototype

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.mapping.config.CPrototype
All Implemented Interfaces:
Weighted
public class CPrototype extends Object implements Weighted
Defining basic properties for an object in the simulation. All possible properties of objects are available. Only the ones needed will be used (for example an RSU does not have a length, so this property would be ignored).

If these values are not defined some default values might be applied depending on prototype type.

  • Field Details

    • name

      public String name
      The name of this prototype. This identifier is used to match it against other objects.

    • group

      public String group
      The group name.

    • weight

      public Double weight
      The weight is used to distribute objects between multiple types. All weights do NOT have to add up to 1 or 100. (Example: A vehicle spawner defining a traffic stream contains two prototypeDeserializers with the weights being 4 and 6. The resulting traffic stream will consist to 40% of the one type and 60% of the other)
